CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper August 10, 1946, pg. 18, reads: "Dinner Guests - Dr. and Mrs. Gideon Brown of Kansas City, Mo., were house guests of Dr. and Mrs. Dudley King during Frog Week. Dr. Brown is nationally known as an outstanding surgeon. The couple will motor from here to Atlantic City for an extended vacation. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group, including Dr. Gideon Brown and Mrs. Brown, and possibly Dr. Dudley King and Mrs. King, possibly in North Park Lodge during FROG week
